page.title: 18CARADON FIELD CLUB DOWNDERRY
page.content: THIS YEAR{1985}A NEW CLUB HAS FORMED TO NOTE AND REPORT ON THE WILDLIFE OF THE AREA.DOWNDERRY IS WELL DOCUMENTED NOTABLE PLANTS INCLUDE MILK THISTLE YELLOW BARTSIA,CORNFLOWER,JACKS & THE DUKE OF ARGYLE'S TEA PLANT. MOTHS INCLUDE FALSE MOCHA,DWARF CREAM WAVE, CLOAKED CARPET,CYPRESS PUG,LIME HAWK,SILVER LINED HAWK & HUMMING BIRD HAWK.THE L-ALBUM WAINSCOT NOW BREEDS HERE.BUSH CRICKETS ARE COMMON; GREAT GREEN,GREY & DARK ARE USUALLY FOUND & THIS YEAR ALSO THE OAK BUSH CRICKET. {MAUGEI'S}SHELLED SLUG COMMONLY OCCURS. THE WOODLOUSE{Platyarthrus}IS IN ANT'S NESTS.THE OPILIONID{Dicranopalpus}IS FOUND.AN UNUSUAL IMMIGRANT TERRESTRIAL AMPHIPOD{WOODHOPPER}IS ESTABLISHED. MANY CENTIPEDES OCCUR eg{Cryptops sp.} {& Lithobius pilicornis}. OF BIRDS,MANX SHEARWEATER,GREAT NORTHERN DIVER & GIANT SKUA MAY BE MENTIONED.
